1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:06,470
In this video we are going to learn what is microservices architecture from Martin Fowler.

2
00:00:06,470 --> 00:00:07,760
Microservice article.

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:13,400
We can say that the microservice architecture style is an approach to developing a single application

4
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:20,600
as a suite of small services, each running in its own process and communicating with lightweight mechanism,

5
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:23,540
often an Http or gRPC APIs.

6
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:30,320
So these services are built around business capabilities and independently deployable by fully automated

7
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:31,610
deployment processes.

8
00:00:32,170 --> 00:00:38,050
There is a bare minimum of centralized management of these services, which may be written in different

9
00:00:38,050 --> 00:00:41,800
programming languages and use different data storage technologies.

10
00:00:42,910 --> 00:00:48,580
The microservice architecture is a software design approach that decompose an application into small,

11
00:00:48,580 --> 00:00:52,900
independent services that communicate over well-defined APIs.

12
00:00:54,170 --> 00:01:00,650
Since each service can be developed and maintained by autonomous teams, it is the most scalable method

13
00:01:00,650 --> 00:01:02,300
for software development.

14
00:01:02,570 --> 00:01:06,410
These services are owned by small, self-contained teams.

15
00:01:06,410 --> 00:01:13,340
Microservice architecture make applications easier to scale and faster to develop, enabling innovation

16
00:01:13,340 --> 00:01:14,210
and acceleration.

17
00:01:14,210 --> 00:01:16,340
Time to market for new features.

18
00:01:16,930 --> 00:01:23,020
So we can say that microservice architecture is a cloud native architecture approach, in which application

19
00:01:23,020 --> 00:01:28,120
composed of many loosely coupled and independently deployable similar components.

20
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:35,960
So microservices have their own technology stack included the database and data management model, and

21
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:41,990
they communicate to each other over a combination of Rest APIs, event streaming and message brokers.

22
00:01:41,990 --> 00:01:47,840
And microservices are organized by business capability, with a line of separating services, often

23
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,730
referred as a bounded context.

